===Etymology===
{{etyl|gem}} ''[[adal]]'' (noble) + ''[[berht]]'' (bright); {{etyl|ang}} ''[[Æþelbeorht]]''. It became very popular in 19th century England due to Queen Victoria’s consort, Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha.

